content: Slecht te bedienen app Ik gebruik deze app voornamelijk om het tijdstip van laden te plannen. Dit is verrassend onhandig door BMW in elkaar gezet. Het gebeurt daardoor geregeld dat het laden niet loopt zoals je wilt of dat je lang bezig ben om iets triviaals voor elkaar te krijgen.
replyContent: Hi Wouter! We zullen je verbeterverzoek naar ons product team doorsturen. Probeer om het probleem te verhelpen je auto los te koppelen van de My BMW App en vervolgens weer te koppelen. Neem als het probleem zich blijft voordoen contact op met het BMW Contact Center op +32(0)3 890 5001, om persoonlijke ondersteuning bij het probleem te krijgen.
content_english: "Poorly usable app. I mainly use this app to schedule charging times. This is surprisingly awkward due to BMW’s implementation. The time interval can be set itself, but there's also a dependency on the departure time. Transferring settings to the car takes an incomprehensible amount of time. As a result, charging frequently doesn't run as desired or you spend a long time to achieve something trivial."

"Prima Service"

Great service. The MyBMW App is generally fine, but the BMW Connected Drive is still a bit clunky. The Digital Key works perfectly, a real plus! However, sometimes the connection to the car drops out, especially when using the climate control remotely. Then it says 'Connection failed' – annoying! It’s a shame about those occasional connection problems; otherwise, it’s a really good app. 4 stars."

content: I'm sure most people will find that flashing your headlights, honking your horn or unlocking your car after waiting a full minute are all good fun for the first couple of days. But then you start to wonder why no actual, useful features are offered. Send reminders when fuel is low or when doors are unlocked? Close windows from a distance? Let me send destinations from my calendar to the car, like I used to be able to in the old app? Wake up, add some useful features, or at least bring them back.
content_english: "I’m sure most people will find that flashing your headlights, honking your horn or unlocking your car after waiting a full minute are all good fun for the first couple of days. But then you start to wonder why no actual, useful features are offered. Send reminders when fuel is low or when doors are unlocked? Close windows from a distance? Let me send destinations from my calendar to the car, like I used to be able to in the old app? Wake up, add some useful features, or at least bring them back."

Oh yeah: being able to link a car to multiple accounts would also be a welcome feature.

content: 1. Waar zit de verbetering t.o.v. de connected app? Stelt nog steeds niet veel voor. En zelfs de afbeelding van mijn eigen auto is vervangen door een vage zwarte vlek. 2. De auto staat altijd binnen in mijn parkeergarage, maar de app geeft meestal aan dat hij nog op mijn laatste bezoekadres staat. Gelukkig geeft de app van mijn Beveiligingsinstallatie "Faringwell" de goede plek wél weer. 3 Wat heeft deze app voor zin als je zulke beperkte info uit je boordcomputer krijgt? 4. En waarom kun je niet gewoon een route met tussenpunten (géén stops) plannen? Verdeeld over wél / geen binnenwegen en deze met een eigen naam naar de auto sturen? Met de gratis app van "Here WeGo" zelf op mijn mobiel en PC kan ik al meer dan met dit duur betaalde navigatie systeem.
content_english: 1. Where’s the improvement compared to the Connected app? Still doesn't amount to much. And even the image of my own car has been replaced by a vague black blot. 2. The car is always parked inside my garage, but the app usually indicates that it’s still at my last visited address. Fortunately, the app of my security system "Faringwell" does show the correct location. 3. What’s the point of this app if you get such limited info from your onboard computer? 4. And why can’t you simply plan a route with intermediate stops (no stops), divide it over on/off highways, and send it to the car with a custom name? I can already do more with the free app "Here WeGo" itself on my mobile and PC than with this expensive navigation system.
topics: ui/ux, vehicle status, trip planning, map/navigation, bmw connected ecosystem

content: Följande saknas som finns i t.ex. Volvos app. Fjärrstart, se om bilen används, temperatur vid bilen, veckotimer för värmaren, körjournal där man kan se alla sträckor bilen flyttat sig med tid och förbrukning m.m. En app för en tjänstebil utan möjlighet till körjournal där man kan markera privata och arbetsresor, hur kan det inte finnas? D.v.s. det mesta användbara saknas och är inte så avancerade funktioner men skulle verkligen vara användbart och ge appen högre betyg.
content_english: “The following is missing, as found in, for example, Volvo’s app. Remote start, to see if the car is in use, temperature at the car, weekly timer for the heater, trip log where you can see all distances the car has moved with time and consumption, etc. An app for a company car without the possibility of a trip log where you can mark private and work trips, how can that not exist? I.e., most of the useful things are missing and aren't that advanced functions but would really be useful and give the app a higher rating.”

content: Appens vigtigste funktion er at kunne styre sin opladning af en elbil. Her fejler den totalt. - Man kan ikke indstille mål for opladning. Etc 80% eller 100% - "Opladning i tidsvindue" virker rigtig dårligt. Man SKAL indstille tidspunkt for kørselsstart selvom man har defineret et tidsrum for opladning? Og ofte starter opladningen flere timer tidligere end den tid man har sat, og afsluttes ligeledes flere timer inden man skal afsted. Det betyder at man betaler overpris for strømmen. Dumt.
content_english: The app's most important function is to be able to control the charging of an electric car. Here, it completely fails. - You can’t set charging goals, e.g. 80% or 100%. "Charging within time window" works really poorly. You MUST set a start time for driving even though you've defined a time window for charging? And often the charging starts several hours earlier than the time you’ve set, and also ends several hours before you need to leave. This means you're paying an inflated price for the electricity. Silly.
topics: charging management, ev-specific features, remote controls, notification management

content: Ladeappen er rask og responsiv, men man hopper hele tiden inn og ut av nettsider og tilbake til appen. replyContent: Hei Sammy! Takk for tilbakemeldingen! Vi beklager at du har opplevd problemer med My BMW App! Vi vil videresende din tilbakemelding til vår utviklingsavdeling for videre undersøkelse. - My BMW App Support Team
content_english: The charging app is fast and responsive, but you’re constantly jumping between websites and back to the app. When you reach many of the websites, there’s no text/layout on them, making navigation impossible. Many graphical errors, and it states you have a charging agreement in some places and that you don’t have a charging agreement in others within the app and its websites. Within the app, Ionity’s subscriptions are called "plus" etc., and in the Ionity app they’s called "passport and motion" - Makes no sense.

"Unstable"

"Appen er ustabil, spesielt når den prøver å koble til Connected Drive. Den fryser ofte, og noen ganger må jeg restarte hele iDrive-systemet. Digital Key fungerer heller ikke alltid som den skal, og det er frustrerende. Laster den ned informasjon om bilen, så henger den seg opp. Det er litt bedre nå enn det var i starten, men det er fortsatt mye å fikse. Håper de fortsetter å jobbe med MyBMW App, så den blir mer stabil og pålitelig. Hadde vært fint om man kunne fått bedre oversikt over status på bestilte tjenester og oppdateringer. Får ofte feilmeldinger, spesielt når man prøver å bruke klimaanlegget via appen. 2/5 stjerner."

content: Har hatt BMW app siden 2016 og det er egentlig ganske rart at en så stor aktør ikke klarer å lage noe bedre enn dette - videreutviklingen i disse årene har vært liten. Først og fremst er den utrolig treg i kommunikasjonen med bilen, dernest så feiler det alt for ofte når man skal sette i gang forvarming. Bilen står på samme sted hver gang med god dekning, så det er neppe forklaringen.
content_english: "Have had the BMW app since 2016 and it's really quite strange that such a large player can't manage to create anything better than this - development over these years has been small. Primarily, it's incredibly slow in communication with the car, then it fails far too often when trying to start pre-conditioning. The car is in the same location every time with good coverage, so it’s probably not the explanation."
